column1: ; The units line must be included, use "feet" or "metric" to indicate units
; The horizons line must start with "horizons" in the first column, then list the horizon names
; Each well must list the name, then the x, y, time, depth values for each horizon
; A "#" symbol for time/depth values indicates a pseudo value
;  xy values must be entered for the first horizon, and where absent copy from a subsequent horizon.
; A "#" symbol for x/y values indicates use the value from previous column (useful for vertical wells)
;  empty cells not permitted, enter a #
; -9999 indicates a null value for time/depth
